let formula = foo.circleCalculator(radius, solveFor);
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "concept"
    }}>{`Concept`}</h2>
    <p>{`There are multiple equations that can be applied to circles.
With the circle calculator formula, you can solve for the diameter, area, and circumference. Mathium uses the following equations to achieve this:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`C = 2πr
d = 2r
A = πr²
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`NOTE: The Mathium circle calcluator function uses a total of `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`11`}</inlineCode>{` decimal points for pi. `}<strong parentName="p">{`This is Mathium's Pi...`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`3.14159265359
`}</code></pre>
