function circleFunction(radius, solveFor) {
  let formula = Mathium.circleCalculator(radius, solveFor);
  return formula;
}
// Test the function
console.log(findPerfSquare(423.89, "circumference"));
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "example-3-solve-for-area-with-a-radius-of-28562"
    }}>{`Example 3: Solve for area with a radius of 2.8562`}</h2>
    <p>{`Suppose we have a circle with a radius of `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`2.8562`}</inlineCode>{` and we want to find the area of that circle.
When applying the formula for area, the result would be the following:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`a = πr² = π(2.8562)²
a = 25.63
